<subSubSection id="C36F6539FF81446EEE866F07FDE8FEBB" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCA36B2FF81446EEE866F07FDE8FEBB" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B901EAA0FF81446EEE866F07FEBAFEE6" bold="true" box="[199,324,258,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The plain, red chestnut colour of this large moth is diagnostic, as are the buff-chestnut coloured apically pointed “Y” shaped rami.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F6539FF81446EEE866F4FFA78FBA3" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA36B2FF81446EEE866F4FFEA7FE9E" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1113]" box="[199,345,330,356]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B901EAA0FF81446EEE866F4FFEA7FE9E" bold="true" box="[199,345,330,356]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Description.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA36B2FF81446EEE866F6AFEDBFE73" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1113]" box="[199,293,367,393]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B901EAA0FF81446EEE866F6AFEDBFE73" bold="true" box="[199,293,367,393]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Female.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA36B2FF81446EEE866F96FDE2FD7F" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B901EAA0FF81446EEE866F96FEEEFE57" bold="true" box="[199,272,403,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Head:</emphasis>
Frons and fronto-clypeus densely covered in upright, long, thin, light chestnut coloured scales. Eyes slightly smaller than head capsule. Labial palps three segmented, first and third palpomeres of equal length, second palpomere three times longer, third palpomeres with round apex.All covered in sandy-chestnut scales, lighter distally. Antennae (
<figureCitation id="134E2A37FF81446EEF526FFAFE70FDE0" box="[275,398,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[308,1274,1268,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[302,1285,1266,1912]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Abantiades paradoxa. Antennae of male and female. (Upper) male at one-third to one-half length from base. (a) lateral view, (b) view from distal end.; female at one-third to one-half length from base. (c) lateral view, (d) view from distal end. (Lower); Basal 21 segments of female antennae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521696/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Fig. 12c–d</figureCitation>
) with 72 segments, chestnut coloured and monopectinate. Basal rami short and lobular then distally become bifurcated and “Y” shaped. Arms and stems of subequal length, slightly elliptical in cross section but with flatter distal than proximal faces. Each arm four times longer than wide, lightly covered in fine, colourless setae, longer laterally and apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA36B2FF81446EEE866C8AFDEDFCA7" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B901EAA0FF81446EEE866C8AFED7FD53" bold="true" box="[199,297,655,681]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Thorax:</emphasis>
Dorsally densely covered in long piliform chestnut scales, ventrally slightly lighter. Forewing 
<quantity id="4C8D9B57FF81446EEBC16C8BFF3DFD37" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="75.0">75 mm</quantity>
long. Dorsally, veins reddish hyaline, surface sparsely clothed in chestnut scales, lanceolate anteriorly, lighter, longer and more piliform basally and along dorsum. Ventrally, costa to Sc densely covered in small chestnut scales, then thinly covered in golden chestnut piliform scales. Hindwing; 
<quantity id="4C8D9B57FF81446EED3B6CFFFC36FCEF" box="[890,968,762,789]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="58.0">58 mm</quantity>
long, dorsally all but costa thinly covered in piliform scales, chestnut anteriorly, golden elsewhere. Ventrally as forewing. Legs densely covered in chestnut scales. Arolium broadly elliptical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA36B2FF81446EEE866D63FDAAFC5F" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B901EAA0FF81446EEE866D63FEBBFC7A" bold="true" box="[199,325,870,896]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Abdomen:</emphasis>
All sternites and tergites densely covered in long piliform scales. Lighter coloured than thorax. Dorsally golden straw, ventrally lighter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA36B2FF81446EEE866DABFA78FBA3" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B901EAA0FF81446EEE866DABFEC1FC32" bold="true" box="[199,319,942,968]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Genitalia:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="134E2A37FF81446EEF116DAAFE30FC33" box="[336,462,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1815,1839]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,1144,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-388@18.[151,1436,1137,1792]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Female genitalia. Abantiades paradoxa, WA, 12 km east of Merredin, 26 April 2014, N. Temby. Dissected M.D. Moore. (a) Posterior view (dorsal plate and lamella antevaginalis), (b) Latero-posterior view dorsal plate, (c) Latero-posterior view antevaginal lamella. Morphological structures: Dp: dorsal plate; Lal: lateral lobe of the antevaginal lamella; Mal: medial lobe of the antevaginal lamella." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521690/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Fig. 10a–c</figureCitation>
). Dorsal plate, moderately sclerotised, bilobed with a large central, regular triangular invagination. Posterior half of plate moderately covered with dark setae. Laterally covered with densely packed, broad and robust scale-like setae (red arrow). Antevaginal lamella with elliptical lateral lobes densely covered in long, scale like setae (red arrow). Medial lobe more sclerotized, subtriangular; two rounded points medially with rounded invagination robust, long, and dark setae medially and dorsal apex; anterior surface partly membranous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF0A663AFF81446EEED66912FE29F861" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521690" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6521690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521690/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" startId="18.[151,250,1815,1839]" targetBox="[162,1424,1144,1782]" targetPageId="18">
